                            <comment id="14520144" author="daijy" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2015 20:25:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4315&quot; title=&quot;MergeJoin or Split followed by order by gives NPE in Tez&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4315&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4315&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14520888" author="rohini" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 05:28:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;daijy&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
   This is not fixed. I was hoping to fix it by rewriting merge join to use broadcast like replicate join, but never got to finish that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14521867" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2015 17:09:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, yes, sorry, I just notice you skip this test in Tez.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14726767" author="rohini" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2015 05:20:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TestPigSplit.testSchemaWithSplit - testcase for Split followed by order by. Have been failing recently. Most likely exposed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4574&quot; title=&quot;Eliminate identity vertex for order by and skewed join right after LOAD&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4574&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4574&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which might have caused getSuccessors to return in a different order. Problem was there earlier as well, but would be successful if sampler operator is connected after partitioner operator instead of the other way round. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14728067" author="daijy" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2015 21:37:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14728100" author="rohini" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2015 21:57:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thanks for the review Daniel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
